    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model to quantify discretization error in the predicted construct stiffness and yield force QoIs. Four mesh densities were evaluated (coarse ~45k elements, medium ~120k elements, fine ~310k elements, extra-fine ~780k elements). The Richardson extrapolation procedure was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI) for each QoI. Results indicated that the fine mesh achieved GCI values below 1.2% for all three QoIs, confirming acceptable discretization error at the selected mesh density. The mesh convergence study was performed independently by two analysts and cross-checked against the Ansys Mechanical default meshing recommendations for contact-bearing titanium alloy assemblies.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
